<subSubSection id="C311653F480A317B9975625DFA5BF9B1" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB436B4480A317B9975625DFC7CFC8C" blockId="73.[810,1458,836,1279]" box="[813,957,836,862]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436B4480A317B9975627DFAABFB6D" blockId="73.[810,1458,836,1279]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">
Phaceloid colony with cylindrical corallites multiplying by extratentacular lateral budding.Radial elements are subcompact, free, straight or wavy septa, organized in 2 distinct size orders. Microstructure typically stylophyllid: septa are made of septal spines linked together by thickening deposits and generally dissociated at the distal and inner edges. 
<collectingRegion id="49CFF856480A317B9EE3651DFB35FBCE" box="[1211,1268,1028,1054]" country="Spain" name="Ceuta" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">Septa</collectingRegion>
show a rhopaloid aspect in transverse section when a septal spine occur in its very inner part. The dissociation of the septal spines along the inner edge sometimes produces a papillose columella.Endotheca made of tabular and vesicular dissepiments. Wall present, apparently parathecal. An epitheca 
<emphasis id="B97FEAA6480A317B9E7D65BAFB81FB6D" box="[1061,1088,1187,1213]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">s.l.</emphasis>
seems to wrap the corallites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436B4480A317B991B65DCFB7EFB2F" blockId="73.[810,1458,836,1279]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">
Calicular diameter: 
<quantity id="4CF39B51480A317B9E4365DCFB50FB0F" box="[1051,1169,1221,1247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3 to 7 mm</quantity>
– Number of septa: 28 to 45 – Septal density: 4 to 5 for 
<quantity id="4CF39B51480A317B9E2E65FCFB7AFB2F" box="[1142,1211,1253,1279]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436B4480A317B9975643FFBBBFAEF" blockId="73.[810,1456,1318,1633]" box="[813,1146,1318,1344]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">SIMILARITIES AND DIFFERENCES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB436B4480A317B9975645EFA5BF9B1" blockId="73.[810,1456,1318,1633]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D37480A317B99E9645EFA50FAB2" authority="(Fromentel, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Fromentel" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[945,1425,1351,1378]" class="Anthozoa" family="Stylophyllidae" genus="Phacelostylophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="B97FEAA6480A317B99E9645EFB0AFAB1" box="[945,1227,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">Phacelostylophyllum martini</emphasis>
(Fromentel, 1860)
</taxonomicName>
by the reduced size of the calices and the mode of budding.The new species has dimensions overlapping with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D37480A317B9E926491FCACFA12" authority="(Duncan, 1867)" baseAuthorityName="Duncan" baseAuthorityYear="1867" class="Anthozoa" family="Stylophyllidae" genus="Phacelostylophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="irregularis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAA6480A317B9E926491FA82FA71" box="[1226,1347,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">P.irregularis</emphasis>
(Duncan, 1867)
</taxonomicName>
. However the Hettangian species of Duncan has a very weak colonial development and a different mode of budding. From other species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D37480A317B9E3564F1FB32F9D1" authority="Vasseur &amp; Lathuilière, 2021" authorityName="Vasseur &amp; Lathuilière" authorityYear="2021" box="[1133,1267,1511,1537]" class="Anthozoa" family="Stylophyllidae" genus="Phacelostylophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="arbustulum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B97FEAA6480A317B9E3564F1FB32F9D1" box="[1133,1267,1511,1537]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">P.arbustulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C57DD480A317B9EA264FEFAF1F9D1" box="[1274,1328,1511,1537]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinctive by its bushlike shape and by low values of diameter for such a number of septa (30-45). 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D37480A317B9E77673EFCADF9B1" authority="(Volz, 1896)" baseAuthorityName="Volz" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Anthozoa" family="Stylophyllidae" genus="Phacelostylophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="romerloana">
<emphasis id="B97FEAA6480A317B9E77673EFAAAF991" box="[1071,1387,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">Phacelostylophyllum romerloana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B45480A317B9F21673EFCA4F9B1" author="VOLZ W." pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" pagination="1 - 127" refId="ref55918" refString="VOLZ W. 1896. - Die Korallen der Trias monographisch bearbeitet. II, in FRECH F. &amp; VOLZ W. (eds), Die Korallen der Schichten von St Cassian in Sud-Tirol. Palaeontographica 43: 1 - 127." type="journal article" year="1896">Volz, 1896</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D37480A317B99F8675EFB76F9B1" authority="(Frech, 1890)" baseAuthorityName="Frech" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[928,1207,1606,1633]" class="Anthozoa" family="Stylophyllidae" genus="Phacelostylophyllum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis id="B97FEAA6480A317B99F8675EFBE3F9B0" box="[928,1058,1607,1632]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258">P. pygmaeum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A4B45480A317B9E77675FFB6EF9B1" author="FRECH F." box="[1071,1199,1606,1633]" pageId="73" pageNumber="1258" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref50674" refString="FRECH F. 1890. - Die Korallenfauna der Trias, 1. Die Korallen der Juvavischen Triasprovinz. Palaeontographica 37: 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1890">Frech, 1890</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
have much less septa.
</paragraph>
